---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const updated = "February 24th 2026";
---

<BaseLayout brand="marysse" title="Cookie Policy">
  <section class="legal-page">
    <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      This Cookie Policy explains how cookies and similar technologies are used on
      <strong>www.maryssedesign.com</strong>.
      Cookies help ensure proper website functionality, improve performance,
      and analyse usage in order to refine the overall experience.
    </p>

    <h2>2. What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website.
      They allow the site to recognise your device and remember certain information
      about your preferences or actions over time.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Categories of Cookies Used</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Essential cookies</strong><br />
        Necessary for the correct functioning and security of the website.
        These cookies do not require user consent.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Analytics cookies</strong><br />
        Used to collect aggregated and anonymised information about how visitors
        interact with the website (e.g. Google Analytics).
        These cookies are activated only after user consent.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong>Affiliate / Marketing cookies</strong><br />
        Used to track referrals through affiliate links, including
        participation in the Amazon Associates Program.
        These cookies may be set by third-party providers.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Google Analytics</h2>
    <p>
      This website may use Google Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google LLC.
      Analytics cookies are activated only after explicit user consent.
      Google may process data on servers located outside the European Union,
      in accordance with applicable safeguards.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      Certain cookies may be set by third-party services integrated into the website,
      such as analytics tools or affiliate networks.
      These third parties are responsible for their own privacy and cookie practices.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Managing or Withdrawing Consent</h2>
    <p>
      You may manage or withdraw your cookie preferences at any time
      by clearing cookies from your browser or revisiting the cookie settings panel.
      Disabling certain cookies may affect website functionality.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Data Transfers</h2>
    <p>
      Some third-party providers (such as Google or Amazon) may process data
      outside the European Union.
      Such transfers are carried out in accordance with applicable data protection regulations.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      This Cookie Policy may be updated periodically.
      Users are encouraged to review this page to stay informed
      about how cookies are used.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For any questions regarding this Cookie Policy, please contact:
      <a href="mailto:info@maryssedesign.com">info@maryssedesign.com</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>